text: Calliotropis reticulina is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Eucyclidae. ==Description== The shell can grow to be 7 mm in length. ==Distribution== It can be found off of the coast of Hawaii. ==References== * Vilvens C. (2007) New records and new species of Calliotropis from Indo-Pacific. Novapex 8 (Hors Série 5): 1–72. ==External links== * reticulina Category:Gastropods described in 1895
title: Calliotropis reticulina
